<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2 leading-tight">Words Ending With -NESS</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 not-prose">2-letter words · 3-letter words · Word of the Day</p>

<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The -NESS suffix is one of Scrabble's most reliable bingo generators. It transforms any adjective into a noun (dark→darkness, quick→quickness) using common tiles that are easy to accumulate. With over 800 valid -NESS words in SOWPODS and the double-S ending providing hook opportunities, this suffix is a cornerstone of competitive play.</p>

<p>The beauty of -NESS is that it uses some of the most common tiles in the bag — N, E, S, S — meaning you'll frequently have the suffix ready without specifically fishing for it.</p>

<p>Tournament players consider -NESS one of the first suffixes to memorize because it produces bingos from almost any adjective root.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why -NESS Matters in Scrabble</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">N(1)+E(1)+S(1)+S(1) base</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">800+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid -NESS words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6–15</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter length range</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>While the base points are modest, the real power of -NESS is volume and accessibility. With 6 N tiles, 12 E tiles, and 4 S tiles in the bag, the odds of holding N-E-S-S are much higher than suffixes requiring scarce letters. This makes -NESS your most dependable bingo path.</p>

